The article is about a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump to honor the memory and public service of Representative Elijah E. Cummings. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government. This is to be done in the District of Columbia, throughout the United States, and its Territories and possessions until October 18, 2019. The proclamation also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The proclamation was signed on October 17, 2019.